               <p>79. 
               
                  <persName id="t17910112-25-defend308" type="defendantName">
                     PETER 
                     SEDDON
                  <interp inst="t17910112-25-defend308" type="surname" value="SEDDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-defend308" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-defend308" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17910112-25-off133" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-off133" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-off133" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a cambrick pocket-handkerchief, value 2 s.
            </rs> the property of the 
               <persName id="t17910112-25-victim309" type="victimName">
                     <rs id="t17910112-25-viclabel134" type="occupation">Right Hon. Lord</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17910112-25-victim309 t17910112-25-viclabel134"></join> Cavan<interp inst="t17910112-25-victim309" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17910112-25-off133 t17910112-25-victim309"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Lord CAVAN sworn.</p>
               <p>The prisoner was servant to me; I sent him on an errand; in the mean time, a pawnbroker came and produced a cambrick handkerchief which was mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179101120036"></xptr>The pawnbroker deposed, that the servant offered him a handkerchief to pawn for a shilling; he looked at it, and saw a coronet upon it, and the prisoner said Lord Cavan gave it to him: he had Lord Cavan's shirt on: he was secured.</p>
               <p>(The handkerchief deposed to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I found the handkerchief as I was going out of the house, I did not know who it belonged to, and I went to pawn it for a shilling.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17910112-25-verdict135" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-verdict135" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17910112-25-punish136" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17910112-25-punish136" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17910112-25-defend308 t17910112-25-punish136"></join>
               Transported for seven years
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the second Middlesex Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
